metadata.name: Acequia #208
metadata.description:
Acequia (‚Äúah-seh-kee-uh‚Äù) - a Spanish adaptation of the Arabic word as-sƒÅqiya, meaning ‚Äúwater carrier‚Äù. 

In our second collaboration, Rich and Rick are back with our blend of generative code, intricate design, attention to detail, and a splash of charm. 

‚Ä®Acequias are traditional irrigation canals used to distribute rainwater and snowmelt along a complex network of narrow channels. They are found in Spain, the American Southwest, and northern Mexico, where they are essential for sustaining fields, orchards, and gardens in semi-arid regions. ‚Ä®‚Ä®
Our aim in this series is to capture the essence of these waterways in bold geometric designs. Each piece is inspired by a mountain village or town in Andalusia (southern Spain). 

The location determines the cube designs and construction rules that are used to build the final output. These are combined with striking day/night palettes, outline styles, scales, climates, and a few surprises of course!


Controls (in live view): 

- Press [p] to pause water animation 
- Press [e] to complete water animation 
- Press [r] to reset water animation 
- Press [s] to save the current image 
- Press [h] for a high-res output suitable for printing 
- Press [b] to toggle the border

metadata.name: Wintosh Computer Club #103
metadata.description:
Welcome to the Wintosh Computer Club, where classic Apple Icons meets the Windows95 color palette.

The WCC is a profil picture project by Drawvolution in collaboration with pixel artist Filter8.
It is a celebration of the nostalgic feeling of the old forgotten classic Computer icon using the 16 colors available in Windows95.


* Size: 64x64 pixel
* Format: .png
* Colors 16
* Layers: 9
* Artworks: 97

* Thanks to PureSpider for the great code.

metadata.name: Henoheno Samurai #2197
metadata.description:
This work was inspired by Otsu-e(Â§ßÊ¥•Áµµ), a Japanese painting in the Edo period. Otsu-e were inexpensive paintings made as souvenirs. Although mass-produced using paper stencils, the artisans painted by hand, resulting in variations in the quality of their work. Connoisseurs found them interesting and collected them as works of art. Otsu-e showed a new value of beauty in Japanese art, different from Ukiyo-e (ÊµÆ‰∏ñÁµµ) which are prints, and from fine art paintings which are one-of-a-kind artworks.

This work is made of canvas2D Bezier curves. Not just a combination of parts, but also a random displacement of the Bezier curve points to lose the shape. This is intended to create fun with the Otsu-e-like effect.


Features:
This profile is made up of 8 parts (brows, eyes, nose, mouth, ear, contour, hair, and body). Each part has 100 basic types. 
There are 7 skin colors and 12 kimono colors. Each RGB value of the colors is randomly added within a range of ¬±10. In addition, there are 70 kimono patterns. 
The distortion rate due to displacement of Bezier curve points is 0.0~50.0. 


BTW The title "Henoheno" is taken from the Japanese character picture "Henohenomoheji" known since the Edo period.

metadata.name: VOODOOZ #307
metadata.description:
Need some luck, happiness, and lucky charm? Alexis Bacci‚Äôs VOODOOZ are here for you! Will you dare to mint and to collect?

VOODOOZ is a collection of 512 magical dolls of 3 types: basic, collector and boss - with or without accessories; a tribute to Voodoo culture entirely hand drawn by the comics author Alexis Bacci.

Each VOODOOZ doll has specific and unique magical powers, bringing luck and happiness, a lucky charm in your journey in the NFTs world!

Voodooz come with optional accessories: the SNAKE, the POTION and the RING.

‚Ä¢ The SNAKE can complete the inner circle of life and vital energy
‚Ä¢ The POTION will help the doll to spell, protect and increase its skills
‚Ä¢ The RING gives more power and can be used as a talisman
‚Ä¢ The HOLY TRINITY gathers the 3 accessories above

Tip: try to grab a SNAKE + a POTION + a RING and a special VOODOOZ NFT will be airdropped to your wallet for free.

Alexis Bacci is a comics book author who has been working in the cartoon and movie industry for two decades. In 2021 he minted his 1st NFTs on ETH, the Tengu Diaries, and his Girlz series on Tezos.

VOODOOZ are Alexis‚Äô genesis series on fx(hash), pay attention!

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #4
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden ‚Äútemplate‚Äù canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‚Äòtemplate‚Äô image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution
